firmware: arm_scmi: preserve rational perf-level frequency scale

Some SCMI firmware uses performance levels that do not divide the sustained
frequency into an integer Hz-per-level multiplier. The current code truncates
the multiplier once and then reuses that truncated value, accumulating small
frequency errors and warning even though the firmware-provided ratio is
coherent.

Store the sustained frequency in Hz and convert non-indexing performance
levels with the original sustained_freq/sustained_perf ratio. Convert Hz
requests back to the closest performance level so OPP frequencies round-trip
to the levels that firmware advertised. Keep the existing 1000 multiplier
fallback for level-indexing/indicative-frequency domains and malformed
attributes.

